data.text:
İzmir, Turkey's third-largest city, is situated on the western coast of the country, at the head of the Gulf of İzmir. The city has a rich history and heritage, dating back to the ancient Greeks, who founded it in the 11th century BC. İzmir's climate is Mediterranean, with hot, dry summers and mild, wet winters.
